  "texts": [
    "For each d ∈ Z, we define N d ⊂ N to be the subset of equivalence classes of polystable SL 2 (R)-Higgs bundles with tr Φ 2 = 0 and deg L = d. If (L, β, γ) is polystable, then |d| < g -1 (cf.",
    "the proof of [Hit87, Prop.",
    "10.2]), so we assume this from now on.",
    "Moreover, there is an det -1 (±1)-gauge transformation (see [Col20, §3.2]) that gives an isomorphism of (L, β, γ) with (L -1, γ, β), so we may assume d ≥ 0.The Higgs vector bundle corresponding to (L, β, γ) is E = L ⊕ L -1 with the Higgs field Φ = 0 β γ 0.The condition 0 = tr Φ 2 = βγ + γβ implies that either β = 0 or γ = 0.",
    "If d > 0, polystability implies γ ̸ = 0 since L would be Φ-invariant if γ = 0."
  ],
